relationships.description: WetWellControlSystem uses PumpControlUnit to manage pumps
WetWellControlSystem uses ControlDisplayPanel to display depth

WetWellControlSystem uses Buzzer for audible alarms
WetWellControlSystem uses LevelSwitches to indicate when to start pumps

domain_model.plantuml:
@startuml
class WetWellControlSystem {
  + monitorLiquidLevel()
  + monitorPumpState()
  + activateAlarm()
  + switchPump(pump: SubmersiblePump, state: boolean)
  + provideAutomatedOperation()
  + provideLocalManualOverride()
  + provideLocalObservationalOperation()
  + startPumpMotors()
  + stopPumpMotors()
  + trackMotorRunningState()
  + monitorUnauthorizedEntry()
  + monitorEnvironmentalConditions()
  + monitorPumpPhysicalCondition()
  + displayOperationalParameters()
  + equalizeRunTime()
  + setAlarmState()
}

class SubmersiblePump {
  + isRunning: boolean
  + isAvailable: boolean
  + hasSealFailure: boolean
  + hasHighTemperature: boolean
  + turnOff()
  + startAlternativeMotor()
}

class PumpControlUnit {
  + startPumpMotors()
  + stopPumpMotors()
  + trackMotorRunningState()
  + trackMotorAvailability()
  + notifyExcessMoisture()
  + notifyOverheat()
  + monitorPumpingSite()
  + recordOperationalParameters()
  + provideAlarmFeature()
  + displayOperationalParameters()
}

class ControlDisplayPanel {
  + depthInFeet: float
}

class FloatSwitch {
  + setLeadPumpState()
  + setLagPumpState()
  + setAlarmState()
}

class IndicatorLight {
  + enable()
}

class Buzzer {
  + sound()
}

class MoistureSensor {
  + detectSealFailure()
}

class LevelSwitch {
  + indicateStart()
}

WetWellControlSystem "1" -- "1..*" SubmersiblePump
WetWellControlSystem "1" -- "1" PumpControlUnit
SubmersiblePump "1" *-- "1" MoistureSensor
PumpControlUnit "1" -- "1..*" SubmersiblePump
FloatSwitch "1" -- "1..*" SubmersiblePump
WetWellControlSystem "1" -- "1" ControlDisplayPanel
WetWellControlSystem "1" -- "0..*" IndicatorLight
WetWellControlSystem "1" -- "1" Buzzer
WetWellControlSystem "1" -- "1..*" LevelSwitch
@enduml

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The design of the wet well control system shall provide for the safety and protection of pumping station operators, maintenance personnel, and the public from hazards that may result from its operation.

issues.description: The requirement is too vague about what specific hazards it aims to protect against and how.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the types of hazards (e.g., electrical, mechanical, chemical) and the mechanisms for protection (e.g., alarms, automatic shutdowns).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall activate a visual and audible alarm when a hazardous condition exists.

issues.description: The term 'hazardous condition' is not defined, leading to potential ambiguity in implementation.
issues.suggested_fix: Define what constitutes a hazardous condition (e.g., high liquid level, pump seal failure, unauthorized entry).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation.

issues.description: The scope of 'automated operation' is not clearly defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the aspects of the system that should be automated (e.g., pump control, alarm activation).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide local manual override operation.

issues.description: The term 'local manual override' is not defined, leading to potential ambiguity in implementation.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the scope of manual override (e.g., pump control, alarm silencing).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide local observational operation.

issues.description: The term 'local observational operation' is not defined, leading to potential ambiguity in implementation.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify what observational operations are required (e.g., viewing pump states, alarm history).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall start the pump motors to prevent the wet well from running over and stop the pump motors before the wet well runs dry.

issues.description: This requirement conflicts with REQ-021, which assigns the same responsibility to the PumpControlUnit.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify which component (WetWellControlSystem or PumpControlUnit) is primarily responsible for starting/stopping pumps.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide an alarm feature.

issues.description: This requirement is redundant with REQ-032, which assigns the same responsibility to the PumpControlUnit.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify which component (WetWellControlSystem or PumpControlUnit) is primarily responsible for the alarm feature.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide a manual override of the site.

issues.description: This requirement is redundant with REQ-009, which also mentions manual override.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge these requirements or clarify the distinction between them.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation of the site.

issues.description: This requirement is redundant with REQ-008, which also mentions automated operation.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge these requirements or clarify the distinction between them.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Monitor and detect prohibited entry to the wet well through the access door by way of broken electrical circuit. Both audible and visible alarms shall be activated.

issues.description: The mechanism for detecting prohibited entry ('broken electrical circuit') is unclear.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify how the electrical circuit is monitored and what constitutes a 'broken' state.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Monitor and detect prohibited entry by way of a broken electrical circuit. Both audible and visible alarms shall be activated.

issues.description: This requirement is nearly identical to REQ-033, leading to redundancy.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge these requirements or clarify the distinction between them.

domain_model_issues.description: The class lacks attributes to store operational parameters (e.g., alarm thresholds, pump run times).
The class lacks attributes to track run time, which is needed for equalizing run times (REQ-020, REQ-026).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an attribute 'runTime' to track the cumulative run time of each pump.

domain_model_issues.description: The class lacks attributes to store historical operational parameters (REQ-031, REQ-037).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes such as 'historicalParameters' to store recorded data.

domain_model_issues.description: The class lacks methods to update the displayed depth and other parameters.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add methods like 'updateDepth(float depth)' to reflect real-time changes.

domain_model_issues.description: The relationship implies a 1:1 association, but REQ-021 suggests PumpControlUnit should manage pumps independently.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Revise the relationship to reflect that PumpControlUnit may operate independently or clarify the dependency.

domain_model_issues.description: The class lacks attributes to store depth thresholds (e.g., leadPumpDepth, lagPumpDepth, highLiquidDepth).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes to store these thresholds and methods to configure them.

domain_model_issues.description: The class lacks attributes to distinguish between different alarm states (e.g., pump running, seal failure, high temperature).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an attribute 'alarmType' to differentiate between alarm states.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for defining the thresholds for lead pump depth, lag pump depth, and allowable high liquid depth
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall allow configuration of the lead pump depth, lag pump depth, and allowable high liquid depth thresholds.
missing_requirements.rationale: The FloatSwitch class sets states based on liquid depth thresholds, but there's no requirement specifying how these thresholds are defined or configured.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system initialization and startup sequence
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall perform a startup sequence that includes self-checks of all sensors, pumps, and alarm systems before entering normal operation mode.
missing_requirements.rationale: Critical systems typically have defined startup sequences to ensure all components are operational before beginning normal operation.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system shutdown or emergency stop
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall provide an emergency stop function that immediately stops all pumps and activates all alarms when triggered.
missing_requirements.rationale: Safety-critical systems require defined emergency procedures.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for data retention period of historical operational parameters
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall retain historical operational parameters for a minimum of 30 days.
missing_requirements.rationale: While requirements mention recording historical data, they don't specify retention periods which are important for maintenance and troubleshooting.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system response time for pump activation/deactivation
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall respond to level changes by activating or deactivating pumps within 5 seconds of reaching the defined thresholds.
missing_requirements.rationale: Performance requirements are missing for this time-critical operation.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for pump maintenance mode
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall support placing individual pumps into maintenance mode, during which the pump will not be automatically activated and alarms related to this pump will be suppressed.
missing_requirements.rationale: Maintenance procedures require the ability to take pumps offline without triggering alarms.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system diagnostics and self-testing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall perform periodic self-tests of all sensors, pumps, and alarm systems, and report any failures.
missing_requirements.rationale: Critical systems typically have diagnostic capabilities to detect component failures.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for handling power failures
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall maintain critical alarm functionality for at least 4 hours during power failure and shall restore normal operation automatically when power is restored.
missing_requirements.rationale: Power failure handling is essential for critical infrastructure systems.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for remote monitoring capability
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall provide capability for remote monitoring of all operational parameters and alarm states.
missing_requirements.rationale: Modern control systems typically include remote monitoring capabilities.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for access control to manual override functions
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall require authentication before allowing access to manual override functions.
missing_requirements.rationale: Safety-critical manual operations should be protected from unauthorized access.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for pump alternation logic
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall alternate the lead/lag pump designation after each pumping cycle to ensure equal wear.
missing_requirements.rationale: While equalizing run time is mentioned, the mechanism for alternation isn't specified.

missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall provide a means to acknowledge alarms, which shall silence the audible alarm while maintaining the visual indication until the alarm condition is cleared.
missing_requirements.rationale: Alarm systems typically include acknowledgment functionality.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for temperature monitoring thresholds
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall allow configuration of temperature thresholds that trigger high temperature alarms and pump shutdown.
missing_requirements.rationale: Temperature monitoring is mentioned but thresholds aren't specified.

missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall maintain an event log recording all state changes, alarms, and operator actions with timestamps.
missing_requirements.rationale: Audit logs are important for troubleshooting and incident investigation.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for pump performance monitoring
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall monitor and record pump performance metrics including flow rate and power consumption.
missing_requirements.rationale: Performance monitoring helps detect pump degradation before failure occurs.
